    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-09-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-09-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="159"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                <head ana="#head_untitled-missing-head-in-printed-volume">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 5644.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States of America</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Department of State</hi>
                        </placeName>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>To all to whom these presents shall come, greeting:</p>
                <p>I certify that the document hereunto annexed is under the seal of the Treasury
                    Department and is entitled to full faith and credit.</p>
                <p>In testimony whereof I, John Hay, Secretary of State of the United States, have
                    hereunto subscribed my name and caused the seal of the Department of State to be
                    affixed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">Done at the city of
                            <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            calendar="gregorian us-republic" when="1900-09-13">this 13th day of
                            September, A. D. 1900, and of the independence of the United States of
                            America the one hundred and twenty-fifth</date>.</dateline>
                    <lb/> (Signed) <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <seg rendition="#left">[Seal: “Department of State of the United States of
                        America.”]</seg>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
